<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1931,2037]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,1931,1957]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
These small specimens (about 4.0 mm) are conveniently distinguished from congeners by having two small black setal tufts near the elytral apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1931,2037]" lastBlockId="22.[151,1436,152,578]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,353,2011,2037]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Description:</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity box="[449,562,2011,2037]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="4.2">4. 2 mm</quantity>
; width 
<quantity box="[660,760,2011,2037]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[777,842,2011,2036]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Form</emphasis>
: Short oblong rectangulate. 
<emphasis box="[1199,1331,2011,2036]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Integument</emphasis>
: Mostly brown, cranial vertex with two brown setal tufts, legs yellow and with brown infuscations, elytra admixture of light brown and dark brown regions, elytral setae yellow, dark brown, or black, two black setal tufts near the elytral apex. 
<emphasis box="[305,368,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Head</emphasis>
: Eyes large, very convex; vertex between eyes broad. 
<emphasis box="[1017,1101,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Thorax</emphasis>
: Pronotal side margins with slightly-developed tubercle, anterior transverse depression not prominent, disc roughly sculptured and with coarse punctations; elytral side margins parallel to posterior four-fifths, then acutely rounded to apex; disc subcorrugated and coarsely punctate. 
<emphasis box="[593,703,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Female pygidium transverse.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,152,578]" box="[198,629,391,418]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,325,391,417]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Variation:</emphasis>
One specimen examined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,152,578]" box="[198,1077,431,458]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,400,431,457]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Natural history:</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[461,563,432,458]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen was collected in June, at 
<quantity box="[981,1073,432,458]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.646" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="m" value="1646.0">1646 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
