<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,152,578]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,511,537]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a Latin compound name formed from 
<emphasis box="[1067,1090,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">bi</emphasis>
(= two) and 
<emphasis box="[1242,1312,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">barba</emphasis>
(= beard). It refers to the two black setal tufts near the elytra apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
